  "prompt": "What is realistic fiction?",
  "response": "Realistic fiction is a genre of literature that depicts stories that could happen in real life, featuring characters, settings, and events that are believable and reflect everyday human experiences. These stories are set in the real world and deal with situations that are plausible and could potentially occur. Key characteristics include:\n\n1. Believable characters with realistic personalities and behaviors\n\n2. Plots that reflect common human experiences and challenges\n\n3. Settings that resemble actual places and time periods\n\n4. Narrative style that feels authentic and genuine\n\n5. No supernatural or fantastical elements\n\n6. Focus on human relationships, emotions, and personal growth\n\n7. Often addresses social issues or personal struggles\n\nExamples of realistic fiction include novels like \"To Kill a Mockingbird\" by Harper Lee, \"The Fault in Our Stars\" by John Green, and \"The House on Mango Street\" by Sandra Cisneros. These works typically aim to explore human nature, society, and personal experiences in a way that feels true to life.\n\nRealistic fiction can be found in various age categories, from children's books to adult novels, and often helps readers understand complex human emotions and social dynamics.",
